# Accessibility Best Practices

## Description

This guide provides comprehensive accessibility guidelines following WCAG 2.1/2.2 standards to ensure your web applications are usable by everyone, including people with disabilities.

## Why Accessibility Matters

- **Legal Compliance**: Many regions require WCAG 2.1 Level AA compliance
- **Better UX**: Accessible design benefits all users, not just those with disabilities
- **SEO Benefits**: Many accessibility improvements also help search engines
- **Wider Audience**: 15% of the world's population has some form of disability
- **Moral Responsibility**: Everyone deserves equal access to digital content

## WCAG Conformance Levels

- **Level A**: Minimum level of conformance (basic accessibility)
- **Level AA**: Target level for most websites (recommended)
- **Level AAA**: Highest level (not always feasible for all content)

**Recommendation**: Aim for WCAG 2.1 Level AA compliance as a baseline.

