## 2. ARIA Labels and Roles

### When to Use ARIA

ARIA (Accessible Rich Internet Applications) enhances accessibility but should be used carefully:

**First Rule of ARIA**: If you can use a native HTML element, do that instead.

```tsx
// ❌ Bad - Unnecessary ARIA
<div role="button" tabIndex={0} onClick={handleClick}>
  Click me
</div>

// ✅ Good - Native element
<button onClick={handleClick}>
  Click me
</button>
```

### Common ARIA Attributes

#### aria-label

Provides an accessible name when visible text isn't present:

```tsx
<button aria-label="Close dialog">
  <XIcon />
</button>

<input
  type="search"
  aria-label="Search products"
  placeholder="Search..."
/>
```

#### aria-labelledby

References another element's text as the label:

```tsx
<h2 id="dialog-title">Confirm Delete</h2>
<div role="dialog" aria-labelledby="dialog-title">
  {/* Dialog content */}
</div>
```

#### aria-describedby

Provides additional description:

```tsx
<input
  type="password"
  aria-describedby="password-requirements"
/>
<div id="password-requirements">
  Must be at least 8 characters with one number
</div>
```

#### aria-live

Announces dynamic content changes:

```tsx
// For status messages
<div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
  {statusMessage}
</div>

// For urgent alerts
<div aria-live="assertive" role="alert">
  {errorMessage}
</div>
```

**aria-live values:**

- `polite`: Announce when convenient (status updates)
- `assertive`: Interrupt immediately (errors, warnings)

#### aria-hidden

Hides content from screen readers:

```tsx
// Hide decorative icons
<span aria-hidden="true">
  <DecorativeIcon />
</span>
<span>Button Text</span>

// Hide duplicated content
<button>
  <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
  <span>Next Page</span>
</button>
```

### Common ARIA Roles

```tsx
// Navigation landmark
<nav role="navigation">
  {/* navigation links */}
</nav>

// Search landmark
<form role="search">
  <input type="search" />
</form>

// Alert for important messages
<div role="alert">
  Form submitted successfully!
</div>

// Dialog/Modal
<div role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="dialog-title">
  {/* dialog content */}
</div>
```

