## 5. Color Contrast Requirements

### WCAG Contrast Ratios

- **Normal text**: Minimum 4.5:1 (Level AA)
- **Large text** (18pt+ or 14pt+ bold): Minimum 3:1 (Level AA)
- **UI components**: Minimum 3:1 (Level AA)

### Testing Color Contrast

```scss
// ❌ Bad - Insufficient contrast (2.5:1)
.text {
  color: #777777;
  background: #ffffff;
}

// ✅ Good - Sufficient contrast (4.6:1)
.text {
  color: #595959;
  background: #ffffff;
}
```

**Tools to check contrast:**

- Chrome DevTools (Lighthouse audit)
- WebAIM Contrast Checker
- Stark plugin for Figma
- Color contrast analyzer browser extensions

### Don't Rely on Color Alone

```tsx
// ❌ Bad - Color only indicator
<span style={{ color: 'red' }}>Error</span>
<span style={{ color: 'green' }}>Success</span>

// ✅ Good - Color + icon/text
<span style={{ color: 'red' }}>
  <ErrorIcon aria-hidden="true" /> Error
</span>
<span style={{ color: 'green' }}>
  <SuccessIcon aria-hidden="true" /> Success
</span>
```

