## 7. Image Accessibility

### Alt Text Best Practices

```tsx
// ✅ Descriptive alt text
<img
  src="/product.jpg"
  alt="Red leather laptop bag with brass buckles"
/>

// ✅ Decorative images - empty alt
<img
  src="/decorative-line.svg"
  alt=""
  aria-hidden="true"
/>

// ❌ Bad - Redundant text
<img src="/icon.png" alt="Icon of a person" />
<span>User Profile</span>

// ✅ Good - Context aware
<img src="/icon.png" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
<span>User Profile</span>
```

### Alt Text Guidelines

- **Decorative images**: Use `alt=""` and `aria-hidden="true"`
- **Functional images**: Describe the action (e.g., "Search" not "Magnifying glass")
- **Complex images**: Provide longer description via `aria-describedby`
- **Text in images**: Include all text in alt attribute
- **Keep it concise**: Under 125 characters when possible

### Next.js Image Component

```tsx
import Image from "next/image";

// ✅ Always provide alt
<Image
  src="/hero.jpg"
  alt="Team collaborating in modern office space"
  width={1200}
  height={600}
/>;
```

