## 9. Landmark Regions

Use landmarks to help screen reader users navigate:

```tsx
<body>
  <header>
    <nav aria-label="Main navigation">{/* primary navigation */}</nav>
  </header>

  <main>
    <h1>Page Title</h1>

    <section aria-labelledby="section-1-title">
      <h2 id="section-1-title">Section Title</h2>
      {/* section content */}
    </section>

    <aside aria-label="Related articles">{/* sidebar content */}</aside>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <nav aria-label="Footer navigation">{/* footer navigation */}</nav>
  </footer>
</body>
```

### Multiple Landmarks of Same Type

Use `aria-label` to differentiate:

```tsx
<nav aria-label="Main navigation">
  {/* primary nav */}
</nav>

<nav aria-label="Footer navigation">
  {/* footer nav */}
</nav>
```

