## 10. Testing Accessibility

### Automated Testing Tools

1. **Lighthouse** (Chrome DevTools)

   - Run: DevTools → Lighthouse → Accessibility
   - Catches ~40% of accessibility issues

2. **axe DevTools** (Browser Extension)

   - More comprehensive than Lighthouse
   - Provides detailed remediation guidance

3. **WAVE** (Web Accessibility Evaluation Tool)
   - Visual feedback on accessibility issues
   - Browser extension available

### Manual Testing Checklist

- [ ] Navigate entire site using only keyboard
- [ ] Test with screen reader (NVDA/JAWS on Windows, VoiceOver on Mac)
- [ ] Check color contrast of all text
- [ ] Verify all images have appropriate alt text
- [ ] Test forms for proper labeling and error handling
- [ ] Confirm modals trap focus properly
- [ ] Check that all interactive elements have visible focus indicators
- [ ] Verify ARIA attributes are used correctly
- [ ] Test at 200% zoom level
- [ ] Check that animations respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

### Screen Reader Testing

**macOS (VoiceOver):**

- Turn on: Cmd + F5
- Navigate: Control + Option + Arrow Keys
- Read next: Control + Option + A

**Windows (NVDA - Free):**

- Download from nvaccess.org
- Navigate: Arrow Keys
- Read next: Insert + Down Arrow

